HOUSE BILL NO. HB0245
Pen and paper ballots.
Sponsored by: Representative(s) Knapp, Brown, G, Haroldson
and Locke and Senator(s) McKeown
A BILL
for
1 AN ACT relating to elections; requiring counties to use pen
2 and paper as the default method to mark ballots for
3 elections in Wyoming; providing an exception; making
4 conforming amendments; and providing for an effective date.
5
6 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Wyoming:
7
8 Section 1. W.S. 22-13-119 is created to read:
9
10 22-13-119. Paper ballots required; exceptions.
11
12 (a) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, each
13 county shall provide paper ballots and pens as the default
14 method to mark ballots for all in-person voting in all
15 elections in Wyoming. The county clerk shall provide all
1 HB0245

