1 that uses a touch screen to produce a marked paper ballot
2 or ballot card.
3
4 Section 2. W.S. 22-10-102, 22-11-102, 22-21-109 and
5 22-22-203(b) are amended to read:
6
7 22-10-102. Selection by county commissioners.
8
9 Subject to the limitations of W.S. 22-13-119, the board of
10 county commissioners may adopt for use in any precinct in
11 the county a type of voting machine meeting the standards
12 specified in W.S. 22-10-101.
13
14 22-11-102. Use authorized; purchase or lease.
15
16 Subject to the limitations of W.S. 22-13-119, the board of
17 county commissioners of each county may adopt for use,
18 either experimentally or permanently, in any election in
19 any or all polling places within the county, any electronic
20 voting system authorized by law.
21
22 22-21-109. Supplies; regulations; costs.
23
